OL,3,CEnergy bills to rise by more than #200
OL,4,Cper year as Iran war impacts households
OL,6,FHowever, the lack of further action on
OL,7,Fenergy bills is seen by some experts
OL,8,Fas holding back spending by cash-
OL,9,Fstrapped consumers.
OL,11,FEconomist Martin Beck, at WPI
OL,12,FStrategy, said recent official figures
OL,13,Fshowing lower retail sales in April
OL,14,Fwas already a sign that "energy
OL,15,Fpressures are biting".
OL,17,F"Higher petrol prices, the prospect of
OL,18,Fan increase in household energy bills
OL,19,Fin July and weakening consumer
OL,20,Fsentiment all point to a more cautious
OL,21,Fspending backdrop," he added.
OL,26,@vD@YOUwD@UO]yD@AOU}D@SO]
